<h1 id="install-parrot-os">Install Parrot OS</h1>

<ol>
  <li>When you power on the VM, you will be asked to select a start up disk. Click the folder icon to open the Optical Disk Selector, click â€˜Addâ€™, and locate the .iso file you downloaded earlier</li>
  <li>Make sure the Parrot OS .iso is selected, then select â€˜Chooseâ€™</li>
  <li>Select â€˜Startâ€™, and wait for the OS to boot automatically or press your Enter key when you see the Try/Install option</li>
  <li>Double click â€˜Install Parrotâ€™ on the desktop</li>
  <li>In the Parrot OS Installer, select your timezone, select â€˜Erase Diskâ€™ in Partitions, and enter your desired username and password in the Users tab. Then select â€˜Installâ€™, â€˜Install Nowâ€™, and â€˜Finishâ€™ once the installation is complete</li>
  <li>Restart the VM and login!</li>
</ol>

<h1 id="connect-to-tryhackme-with-openvpn">Connect to TryHackMe with OpenVPN</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Open a browser, navigate to tryhackme.com and login.</li>
  <li>Click on your user icon in the top right hand corner, and select â€˜Accessâ€™ from the drop down menu.</li>
  <li>Select a VPN server and click on â€˜Download My Configuration Fileâ€™</li>
  <li>Save <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;YOUR USERNAME&gt;.ovpn</code> in an easy to remember location</li>
  <li>In a terminal, enter the command <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo openvpn &lt;FILEPATH&gt;</code>, where FILEPATH is the location of your .ovpn file. You should see <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Initialization Sequence Completed</code> if the connection is successful. Keep this terminal open in the background while youâ€™re interacting with TryHackMeâ€™s vulnerable machines, closing it will terminate the connection.
<img src="/images/openvpn.png" alt="OpenVPN" /></li>
</ol>

